# TierZero — AI IT Ticket Resolution Agent

TypeScript (Node 18+, ESM), LangGraph, LangChain, OpenAI, ChromaDB. No framework. No build step — `tsx` runs source directly.

## What it does

Reads tickets from ServiceNow / Jira / GitLab, searches a RAG knowledge base, then decides: `automate` | `draft_response` | `escalate` | `needs_info`. One structured LLM call decides, then the agent executes deterministically. No open-ended tool loops.

## Agent flow (strict linear graph)

```
START → ingest → retrieve → decide → act → record → END
```

Defined in `src/agent/agent.ts` as a LangGraph `StateGraph`. The `decide` node makes a single structured LLM call (Zod schema). The `act` node executes deterministically based on the decision.

## TicketConnector pattern

All ticketing systems implement `TicketConnector` from `src/connectors/connector.ts`. The interface has: `listTickets`, `getTicket`, `getComments`, `addComment`, `listAttachments`, `downloadAttachment`, `uploadAttachment`, `updateTicket`. Adding a connector = implement that interface, nothing else.

Current connectors: `servicenow.ts`, `jira.ts`, `gitlab.ts`.

`TicketStatus` is a strict union: `"open" | "in_progress" | "pending" | "resolved" | "closed"`. Every connector must map to these — never invent new values.

## Knowledge ingest pipeline

`src/ingest/` importers write `.md` files to `knowledge/`, then the user runs `npm run index`. Importers: `azure-devops.ts` (wiki + work items), `confluence.ts`, `url-scraper.ts`, `ticket-miner.ts`. Shared utilities in `src/ingest/types.ts` (`htmlToMarkdown`, `slugify`, `writeIfChanged`).

## Testing conventions

- Framework: `node:test` + `node:assert/strict` — NOT vitest or jest
- Only test pure helpers — no mocked HTTP, no real network calls
- Export testable functions via `_testExports` or named exports from the module
- Test files live next to source: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts`
- Run: `npm test` (uses `tsx --test`)

```typescript
// ✅ correct test imports
import { describe, it } from "node:test";
import assert from "node:assert/strict";
```

## Code conventions

- Local imports use `.js` extension (ESM): `import { foo } from "./bar.js"`
- No new dependencies without strong justification — `fetch`, `crypto`, `fs/promises` cover most needs
- `async/await` throughout, no callbacks
- No comments that narrate what the code does — only non-obvious intent or constraints

## Key files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `src/agent/agent.ts` | LangGraph StateGraph, AgentState, decision schema, 7 tools |
| `src/agent/poller.ts` | Continuous polling loop |
| `src/connectors/connector.ts` | TicketConnector interface |
| `src/connectors/types.ts` | Ticket, TicketComment, TicketStatus, etc. |
| `src/rag/indexer.ts` | Chunk + embed + upsert to ChromaDB |
| `src/rag/retriever.ts` | MMR / similarity search |
| `src/ingest/types.ts` | htmlToMarkdown, slugify, writeIfChanged |
| `src/cli.ts` | All CLI commands |

## Environment

ChromaDB must be running (`docker run -p 8000:8000 chromadb/chroma`) before any RAG or indexing commands. `OPENAI_API_KEY` is always required. See `.env.example` for all variables.
